          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Richmond</placeName> Erab
                                                  <add>?</add>.H. <date>5612</date></p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Esteemed Friend!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Your last kind favour<lb/> came duly to hand, and,
                                        its contents noted,<lb/> and would have replied on its
                                        receipt<lb/> had it have been urgent, but I supposed<lb/>
                                        that my silence indicated to you that we<lb/> would defer
                                        the publication of the testimony.<lb/> I wish that it were
                                        in my power to pay the<lb/>
                                        <sic>the</sic>
                                        <sic>expence</sic> of this printing myself I can assure<lb/>
                                        you I would do so. I am disgusted at<lb/> the proceedings of
                                        the German congregation, it<lb/> is without exception the
                                        most irreligious<lb/> proceeding I ever heard of, the case I
                                        am<lb/> sure stands <sic>unparralled</sic> in the annals
                                        of<lb/> American congregations, and its leaders are
                                        deser-<lb/>ving of the severest censure.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">You state that probably you will be on<lb/> here
                                        about succoth, I trust you may, we<lb/> will all be pleased
                                        to see you and if<lb/> you come I hope that it may be
                                        your<lb/> pleasure to deliver a discourse at the<lb/>
                                        synagogue of <hi rend="underline">our</hi> congregation. I
                                        should<lb/> like you to let me know at what time<lb/> you
                                        will be on here, exactly the day,<lb/> you expect to
                                        arrive.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>There is nothing of interest a stirring here<lb/> and must conclude
                                        in wishing that you<lb/> may be remembered in the Book-of
                                        Life<lb/> and believe me to remain</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">Your sincere friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">
                                        <persName role="author">Jacob Ezekiel</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Please remember me kindly to all my<lb/> old acquaintances and
                                        particularly to<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mrs Cozzens</persName> and her daughter, and to
                                                  <persName>Mrs<lb/> Hart</persName> &amp;
                                        Family.</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Pa</placeName>
                              </p>
